WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.047
<i>JEREMIAH: Thomas Michael Shelby...</i>

00:02.719 --> 00:04.370
<i>TOMMY". Today is my wedding day.</i>

00:04.920 --> 00:05.921
Take the photograph!

00:06.800 --> 00:09.371
<i>TOMMY". The Russians have made contact.
ARTHUR". On your wedding night.</i>

00:09.440 --> 00:12.011
Whoever it is up there,
he gave the wrong name.

00:12.080 --> 00:13.764
Can you do it?
Can you kill?

00:13.960 --> 00:15.450
You know
why he didn't come, don't you?

00:15.560 --> 00:16.561
My bloody man.

00:16.800 --> 00:18.450
There was a fire at his restaurant.

00:18.560 --> 00:20.847
No fraternizing with the foreigners.

00:20.960 --> 00:22.769
There's a cavalry officer.

00:23.200 --> 00:24.964
In March, we'll be engaged.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.929
<i>JOH</i> N: <i>But you want to try things first.</i>

00:27.680 --> 00:29.489
<i>RUBEN". I'm Ruben Oliver,
portrait artist.</i>

00:30.040 --> 00:31.041
You have my card.

00:31.200 --> 00:33.601
What was in your heart was beautiful.

00:34.600 --> 00:35.601
-(GUNSHOT)
-(PANTING)

00:36.000 --> 00:39.527
just get this business done
and get away from things like this.

00:39.600 --> 00:40.601
Promise me.

00:41.040 --> 00:42.087
I promise.

00:42.720 --> 00:44.085
I will make us safe.

00:45.360 --> 00:47.362
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:55.040 --> 01:56.883
NUTLEY: Your brothers came to my house.

01:58.240 --> 02:01.130
They said the Peaky Blinders
had business with me.

02:03.200 --> 02:05.487
TOMMY: You're not afraid of me.

02:13.680 --> 02:14.681
So,

02:15.480 --> 02:17.881
what is it you want
from a simple working man?

02:18.720 --> 02:19.801
Fear.

02:24.920 --> 02:27.082
Poor Mr Nutley drank too much.

02:28.640 --> 02:32.326
He went for a piss on the train tracks
that run behind the factory.

02:33.040 --> 02:34.280
Train came.

02:36.400 --> 02:38.687
They found his body in Saltley
broken into bits.

02:38.800 --> 02:40.370
I know what you do.

02:41.400 --> 02:42.811
Tell me what you want.

02:48.600 --> 02:49.601
There.

02:50.480 --> 02:54.371
The let's complete warehouse.
Bays 4, 5 and 6.

02:54.560 --> 02:55.846
You have the keys?

02:56.120 --> 02:57.849
Yes, I have keys.

02:59.040 --> 03:00.485
What's in Bay 4?

03:01.560 --> 03:04.962
Completed type 40s and type 21 <i>s</i>
waiting for the paint shop.

03:05.800 --> 03:07.040
Bay 5?

03:07.480 --> 03:09.642
- NUTLEY: Paint shop and parts.
- Uh-huh.

03:10.920 --> 03:12.160
So, it's Bay 6.

03:12.680 --> 03:13.841
What is?

03:14.800 --> 03:15.961
(IN HALES SHARPLY)

03:16.040 --> 03:17.929
Give me the keys to Bay 6.

03:19.600 --> 03:21.250
It's just old stock in storage.

03:22.200 --> 03:24.441
Give me the keys to Bay 6.

03:26.400 --> 03:27.970
(SIGHS)

03:38.400 --> 03:39.925
(KEYS JANGLING)

03:51.560 --> 03:52.766
For your trouble.

03:53.880 --> 03:55.325
Give it to your charity.

04:04.440 --> 04:07.046
I'm only doing this
for the safety of my family.

04:51.360 --> 04:52.407
(GRUNTS)

05:11.080 --> 05:12.411
(SIGHS)

05:12.480 --> 05:13.561
(SNIFFS)

05:31.520 --> 05:32.601
(SIGHS)

05:33.120 --> 05:37.489
HUGHES: So, will it bejust boys in your
charitable institution or girls as well?

05:39.560 --> 05:40.891
Both.

05:42.040 --> 05:43.326
You must divide them.

05:44.320 --> 05:46.448
You know how the little creatures
can get.

05:48.520 --> 05:51.364
Where are your people?
You said they'd be here by 5:00.

05:52.200 --> 05:53.804
HUGHES: They are a law unto themselves.

05:54.440 --> 05:56.807
You can never quite grasp who they are.

05:57.640 --> 05:59.210
Like gripping wet soap-

06:01.440 --> 06:03.169
I've done my research.

06:04.480 --> 06:06.050
Erm...

06:06.200 --> 06:10.171
Perhaps you know them
as the, uh, Economic League.

06:11.040 --> 06:14.408
Only once did I get a letter from them
headed "The Vigilance Committee."

06:14.600 --> 06:16.329
Which tips the hand a little.

06:16.600 --> 06:18.409
(CLICKS TONGUE) No.

06:18.760 --> 06:21.570
The name I've heard is Section D.

06:21.840 --> 06:24.571
-(POURING DRINK)
- That's what Special Branch calls them.

06:25.320 --> 06:29.086
Business men, MPs, army officers.

06:30.880 --> 06:32.166
(EXHALES)

06:33.160 --> 06:36.448
HUGHES: Yes, it will be fun to bring
such men to a Gypsy scrapyard.

06:36.520 --> 06:37.760
(scoffs)

06:39.480 --> 06:41.050
You asked for privacy.

06:41.480 --> 06:45.690
Since the election, the government
has decided that we are the enemy.

06:46.920 --> 06:50.288
When all we're trying to do
is save the country from revolution.

06:52.480 --> 06:54.881
Are you political, Mr Shelby?

06:56.280 --> 06:57.611
Because these Odd Fellows believe

06:57.680 --> 07:01.207
that the time is coming soon
when everyone must choose a side.

07:03.360 --> 07:05.647
Are your people coming
or are they not coming?

07:06.280 --> 07:09.489
Mr Shelby, you will learn that
these men are far too grand

07:09.560 --> 07:11.289
for the clock to govern them.

07:12.840 --> 07:15.923
You'll get used to meeting
in the small hours of the morning.

07:16.680 --> 07:17.806
They're like monks.

07:21.400 --> 07:24.131
So, when is your
charitable institute opening?

07:24.480 --> 07:26.403
(EXHALES) When I fucking say.

07:28.360 --> 07:31.250
Well, I'll stop by from time to time

07:31.320 --> 07:33.641
to hear confession
from the little creatures.

07:35.480 --> 07:38.165
You'll meet Mr Patrickjarvis, MP.

07:38.240 --> 07:40.288
He'll probably want to become a trustee.

07:41.240 --> 07:44.961
It's just his thing, to drop by
in the evenings after a few drinks.

07:45.880 --> 07:50.442
We'll make it a formal arrangement
as part of the bigger deal between us.

07:52.360 --> 07:54.806
- I will have an office there.
-(CLEARING THROAT)

07:57.360 --> 07:58.885
(TOMMY SNIFFS)

08:00.000 --> 08:01.161
(s PITS)

08:02.000 --> 08:03.047
Ah!

08:04.280 --> 08:07.011
My God. Some devil gets into you,
doesn't it, boy?

08:09.680 --> 08:11.330
Mr Shelby,

08:11.880 --> 08:16.886
if I want to play the squire in your
place of false charity, then I will.

08:17.920 --> 08:21.129
Ambition for respectability
doesn't make you a saint.

08:21.720 --> 08:22.926
Am I wrong?

08:24.720 --> 08:26.449
(BELL TOLLING)

08:27.880 --> 08:29.723
Oh, Lord. That's 6:00, is it?

08:31.760 --> 08:34.410
Well, I wish you a good day.

08:35.200 --> 08:36.690
Where the fuck are you going?

08:36.760 --> 08:38.330
Did I not make it clear?

08:39.120 --> 08:41.441
They said if they weren't here
by morning prayers

08:41.520 --> 08:43.328
then the meeting has been cancelled.

08:44.640 --> 08:48.361
Perhaps Mr Jarvis has been held up
at the House of Commons.

08:49.280 --> 08:52.329
Perhaps Admiral Hall's been held up
at the House of Lords.

08:53.440 --> 08:54.805
Am I impressing you?

08:55.960 --> 08:58.725
Or perhaps they have decided
they don't care for doing business

08:58.800 --> 09:00.962
with Gypsies in scrap metal yards

09:01.360 --> 09:03.601
which would be a poor outcome for you.

09:03.680 --> 09:06.206
You give them a message
from me, Priest.

09:08.280 --> 09:10.760
You tell them I've been to the factories

09:11.160 --> 09:13.686
and the armoured vehicles
are in good condition.

09:16.280 --> 09:17.691
HUGHES: How many?

09:19.640 --> 09:21.085
<i>Twenty-seven.</i>

09:21.960 --> 09:23.803
And the foreman is ours.

09:26.240 --> 09:28.049
This is someone you'll meet.

09:28.680 --> 09:30.489
Today, at the Ritz.

09:31.160 --> 09:32.525
I have meetings today.

09:33.040 --> 09:35.691
You have one meeting, this one.

09:36.480 --> 09:37.720
In London.

09:39.120 --> 09:41.009
So, you'd best catch the milk train.

09:48.640 --> 09:50.290
(VIOLIN PLAYING)

09:52.520 --> 09:54.409
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

10:22.280 --> 10:23.964
(VIOLIN STOPS PLAYING)

10:40.120 --> 10:41.121
Cold.

10:41.600 --> 10:42.601
My apologies, sir.

10:42.840 --> 10:44.649
And how many times
I asked you to tell them

10:44.720 --> 10:46.529
about sending us the servant's crockery.

10:46.600 --> 10:48.967
BUTLER: I have no control
over the choice of service, sir.

10:49.040 --> 10:52.601
Hmm, and what about yesterday's eggs
and last year's fish

10:53.000 --> 10:55.287
and last century's tea leaves
in a cracked pot.

10:55.400 --> 10:58.961
Sir, I have a list of today's social
engagements, if you'd like to hear them.

10:59.040 --> 11:00.326
Oh, are we in a rush today?

11:00.440 --> 11:02.204
- I have duties at the main house, sir.
- Mmm.

11:03.480 --> 11:05.482
BUTLER: Luncheon at The Ritz
with Duke Michail Michailovich.

11:06.680 --> 11:07.806
(LEON SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN)

11:07.960 --> 11:09.291
Cancelled.

11:09.760 --> 11:13.401
-(IN ENGLISH) What reason?
- BUTLER: He says he is unwell, sir.

11:15.400 --> 11:17.880
You are due to have tea at 3:00

11:17.960 --> 11:21.851
with Prince Sevlod Ianovich
and Lady Mary Lewington, sir.

11:23.160 --> 11:25.447
Mmm! Good.

11:25.560 --> 11:28.131
I miss out on the bore
and meet the beauty.

11:28.280 --> 11:30.123
However, in the absence of the Duke,

11:30.280 --> 11:34.126
the, er, Prince and the Lady
too have cancelled, sir.

11:37.640 --> 11:40.291
Other than that,
your day is, er, your own.

11:41.760 --> 11:43.569
You do have one business appointment

11:44.120 --> 11:48.728
to discuss automobiles
with a Mr Thomas Shelby, sir.

11:53.640 --> 11:54.926
(HORSE WHINNYING)

12:15.240 --> 12:17.925
You asked for a meeting out in the open.

12:18.720 --> 12:21.769
Fresh air and the fine aroma of shit.

12:23.240 --> 12:24.526
"Neutral ground", you said.

12:25.480 --> 12:27.926
VICENTE: This is hardly neutral ground.

12:28.240 --> 12:31.130
Well, it's what you've got.

12:31.400 --> 12:33.880
<i>So, par fa var,</i>

12:35.160 --> 12:36.161
sit down.

12:36.800 --> 12:38.609
- VICENTE: Where is Thomas?
- He got called away.

12:38.720 --> 12:39.721
He'd said he'd be here.

12:39.840 --> 12:40.841
ARTHUR: Yeah, he is busy.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.401
And I just told you he got called away.
What do you want?

12:49.760 --> 12:51.842
There has been a peace

12:52.680 --> 12:54.170
between the Peaky Blinders

12:54.240 --> 12:56.971
and the Changretta family
for two years now...

12:57.120 --> 12:58.201
Do you want some tea or not?

12:59.880 --> 13:02.724
Here, Finn, pour the Italians
some English tea. Go on.

13:03.880 --> 13:05.769
We don't want fucking tea.

13:10.600 --> 13:12.364
We want an explanation.

13:12.680 --> 13:13.920
Well, I'll have fucking tea.

13:14.320 --> 13:16.049
Explanation for what?

13:16.760 --> 13:20.810
The Little Venice Restaurant
on Forge Street was burnt down.

13:21.200 --> 13:23.441
No. No. Couldn't have been us,
we was at a wedding.

13:23.600 --> 13:28.606
You burnt it down to stop my son
being at that same wedding.

13:28.880 --> 13:30.041
He wasn't missed.

13:30.280 --> 13:31.406
(LAUGHS)

13:32.720 --> 13:33.960
(CHUCKLES)

13:34.800 --> 13:36.609
You are such big boys now.

13:37.480 --> 13:41.280
But once you borrowed clothes from us
to look like men.

13:41.800 --> 13:43.848
- How's the tea, Arthur? Is it...
-(SPLASHES)

13:45.960 --> 13:47.325
It's cold.

13:50.040 --> 13:51.769
Please tell Tommy

13:52.440 --> 13:54.920
that we pay him
whatever he asks us to pay.

13:55.000 --> 13:57.810
We stay out of the city
and off the tracks.

13:58.520 --> 14:01.808
But you tell him from me

14:02.880 --> 14:07.408
that my son will walk
with any woman in this city.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.250
Any woman he chooses.

14:09.720 --> 14:13.486
Even if that woman works
for the emperor, Thomas Shelby.

14:13.960 --> 14:15.610
My son is in love...

14:15.960 --> 14:17.200
(JOHN SNORTS)

14:17.720 --> 14:20.291
JOHN: (CHUCKLING) Sorry. Do excuse me.

14:20.960 --> 14:23.247
(SNIFFS) Carry on.

14:26.880 --> 14:31.363
VICENTE: And if he wishes,
he will walk with the woman he loves.

14:31.840 --> 14:32.841
OK.

14:34.600 --> 14:35.806
You know...

14:36.400 --> 14:38.721
It would be hard for your son
to walk anywhere

14:39.480 --> 14:41.881
with a bullet in each knee, wouldn't it?

14:50.040 --> 14:51.121
Too much.

14:53.360 --> 14:55.567
You said too much, my friend.

14:56.520 --> 14:59.205
Sabini says, "Suck and swallow." But no.

15:00.320 --> 15:01.321
Too much.

15:02.600 --> 15:04.568
I spit. (SPITS)

15:05.120 --> 15:07.248
(VICENTE SPEAKING ITALIAN)

15:10.480 --> 15:13.211
JOHN: Oh. OK. A bit strong.

15:18.680 --> 15:21.160
-(LAUGHS) Fucking hell.
- Isiah.

15:22.280 --> 15:24.965
Put two extra men on our pubs
in Nechells.

15:25.640 --> 15:27.085
What are you talking about, Arthur?

15:27.320 --> 15:29.129
We're not scared of
fucking Eyeties any more.

15:29.280 --> 15:32.523
Don't tell Tommy about the chair
and clean this fucking shit up.

15:34.240 --> 15:36.481
We're not scared of fucking wops!

15:36.640 --> 15:38.005
(GRUMBLES) All right, john.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.331
Arthur!

15:45.680 --> 15:46.886
TOMMY: Hello, Ada.

15:49.920 --> 15:51.604
ADA: Tommy Shelby? In a library?

15:51.680 --> 15:54.524
TOMMY: I need to borrow a book
about the Russian Revolution.

16:02.960 --> 16:05.167
ADA: Have you got a new wharf
at Maida Vale now?

16:05.640 --> 16:07.483
TOMMY: I've got a new wharf
everywhere now.

16:07.840 --> 16:09.888
ADA: Sometimes, I see our trucks
driving past.

16:10.560 --> 16:11.641
TOMMY: "Our" trucks?

16:12.960 --> 16:14.450
Shelby trucks.

16:15.200 --> 16:16.531
Why the interest?

16:17.120 --> 16:19.361
I just want to broaden my mind.

16:20.000 --> 16:22.685
Well, this is a list of the bastards
who ran away.

16:22.760 --> 16:26.526
And this is written from the point of
view of the peoples' struggle.

16:26.600 --> 16:27.806
Uh-huh.

16:29.840 --> 16:31.524
ADA: There was a Russian
at your wedding.

16:33.320 --> 16:35.482
He wouldn't tell me
how come he got invited.

16:39.000 --> 16:44.040
Well, sometimes,
exiled Russian aristocrats get invited

16:45.360 --> 16:47.442
to social occasions to add
a bit of class.

16:47.720 --> 16:49.131
Is that why he was there?

16:50.480 --> 16:51.811
Why do you want to know?

16:53.040 --> 16:55.771
He was nice.
Maybe I'd like to see him again.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.285
Would that be possible?

16:58.160 --> 16:59.571
No. That would not be possible.

16:59.640 --> 17:01.961
What business do you have
with the Russians, Tommy?

17:04.560 --> 17:05.560
Can I rip this page out?

17:05.640 --> 17:07.130
No, you cannot rip that page out.

17:07.200 --> 17:08.565
- Property of the people.
-(SIGHING)

17:08.800 --> 17:10.290
Tommy, when Arthur
took the Russian away,

17:10.359 --> 17:11.805
he had his killing pistol
under his jacket.

17:11.880 --> 17:14.121
And then johnny lit a fire in the woods.

17:15.880 --> 17:18.359
You want all the details
because you're bored, Ada.

17:21.119 --> 17:23.726
You used to chase rats
with a revolver, Ada.

17:23.800 --> 17:25.689
-(PEOPLE SHUSHING)
-(SOFl'LY) For fuck's sake.

17:25.839 --> 17:28.319
I mightjust have a job for you
after all.

17:28.440 --> 17:29.521
(SIGHS)

17:37.160 --> 17:39.208
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

17:56.360 --> 17:58.089
Did we run Kempton yesterday or not?

17:58.680 --> 18:00.091
Danny Lee got drunk.

18:00.720 --> 18:02.370
Instead of injecting the horses
with cocaine,

18:02.440 --> 18:03.930
he decided to share it with his cousins.

18:05.120 --> 18:07.043
(SIGHS) Jesus Christ.

18:07.280 --> 18:09.123
He's your brother-in-law.

18:09.240 --> 18:11.083
Tell Esme to speak to him about it.

18:11.600 --> 18:14.524
Look. Before I start...

18:17.480 --> 18:19.482
I don't want you to do anything
about this.

18:20.800 --> 18:21.926
About what?

18:24.160 --> 18:25.321
Vicente Changretta's son.

18:26.280 --> 18:29.363
- The one Lizzie was stepping out with...
- What, Angel?

18:29.480 --> 18:31.528
He's no bigger
than twopence worth of change.

18:31.680 --> 18:34.251
Well, he heard you threatened him
directly to shoot him in the knees.

18:34.320 --> 18:35.526
And now he's going around Nechells

18:35.600 --> 18:37.011
telling everybody
he's going to kill you.

18:38.640 --> 18:41.803
This is Lizzie's fault to start with,
Tommy's for leaving it up to you.

18:41.920 --> 18:43.285
What are you talking about?

18:44.600 --> 18:45.840
We run London.

18:46.240 --> 18:48.208
We run the north,
we run the whole fucking country.

18:48.320 --> 18:50.607
What do we care about
some fucking Nechells Green Eyeties?

18:50.680 --> 18:53.206
We don't need to be getting involved
in all these little piss pots.

18:53.520 --> 18:54.601
What does Arthur say?

18:55.680 --> 18:58.843
That's why I'm here and not him.

18:59.920 --> 19:01.684
If he said it, there'd be a fight.

19:02.520 --> 19:03.521
He says,

19:05.120 --> 19:06.281
"Apologise."

19:08.280 --> 19:09.520
(SNIFFS)

19:10.240 --> 19:11.890
He fucking said what?

19:12.240 --> 19:14.083
POLLY: We own the city.

19:14.520 --> 19:16.727
But we don't need to rub
everybody's noses in it.

19:17.080 --> 19:18.650
If the old man decides to make a stand,

19:18.720 --> 19:20.290
he might get Sabini
feeling sentimental...

19:20.360 --> 19:21.885
JOHN: Sabini's done.

19:25.680 --> 19:27.091
They're all done.

19:28.400 --> 19:30.323
And they all pay UP-

19:31.760 --> 19:35.731
But we don't want rebellions.

19:36.000 --> 19:37.126
(SIGHS)

19:38.040 --> 19:40.441
What does, erm, Tommy say?

19:40.720 --> 19:42.927
Tommy's busy. He left me in charge.

19:43.400 --> 19:44.640
And what do you say?

19:49.200 --> 19:51.043
- Compromise.
- Mmm-hmm.

19:52.600 --> 19:54.170
I've asked Lizzie to do it for you.

19:54.600 --> 19:56.967
She's going to meet him,
break up with him for good,

19:57.040 --> 19:59.520
apologise for any inconvenience,
say it was all her fault...

19:59.600 --> 20:01.011
- For fuck's sake!
-(CLATl'ERING)

20:02.880 --> 20:04.450
You know what all this is?

20:04.640 --> 20:06.324
This is Arthur's fucking missus.

20:06.760 --> 20:08.649
Turn the other fucking cheek?

20:09.200 --> 20:12.443
We'll be handing out Bibles in the
fucking Bull Ring with her cousins.

20:12.520 --> 20:16.286
John, you don't have to do anything.
Lizzie will do it for you.

20:16.360 --> 20:19.842
Then it'll all calm down
and nobody will lose face.

20:19.920 --> 20:21.649
I'll take his fucking face.
How about that?

20:21.720 --> 20:23.449
-(DOOR SLAMS)
-john, do nothing... (SIGHING)

20:32.520 --> 20:35.126
I believe you have a reservation
for a private room

20:35.200 --> 20:36.611
in the name of Mr Romanov.

20:39.240 --> 20:40.480
(CLICKS TONGUE)

20:40.560 --> 20:42.005
You work for Mr Romanov?

20:43.600 --> 20:45.887
- Yes.
- For his household or his office?

20:46.280 --> 20:47.884
(SIGHING) Is there a problem?

20:47.960 --> 20:50.122
I'm afraid without the presence
of the Duke Mikhail Michailovich

20:50.200 --> 20:55.969
or Lady Lewington, we shall have to ask
for payment in advance.

20:56.800 --> 20:57.801
Can I ask why?

20:58.280 --> 21:01.409
Already, Mr Romanov
has four outstanding bills with us.

21:01.880 --> 21:03.928
One for accommodation
and three for dining.

21:04.120 --> 21:07.090
And two banquets, which we wrote off.

21:07.280 --> 21:10.648
We've been asked to be understanding
of our Russian friends by His Majesty.

21:10.720 --> 21:13.007
- But it has been some time now...
-(THUDS)

