46:08.920 --> 46:11.127
You promised, Tommy.

46:11.200 --> 46:12.770
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

46:12.840 --> 46:14.649
I trust you.

46:17.520 --> 46:19.204
- I trust you, Tommy.
- Yes.

46:22.000 --> 46:24.810
(SOFTLY) He's fine. He's fine.

46:26.000 --> 46:27.764
(CHARLIE CRYING)

46:35.120 --> 46:37.168
Grace. Grace.

46:38.240 --> 46:39.810
(WHISPERING) Come on.

46:53.680 --> 46:55.489
You're not one of those
Impressionists, are you?

46:55.600 --> 46:57.284
They're all terribly political,
aren't they?

46:58.440 --> 47:00.204
- And you're not?
- Goodness no.

47:00.840 --> 47:03.969
The people I work forjust
want me to paint what is there.

47:04.040 --> 47:06.691
To me, politics is deliberately
making things better

47:06.760 --> 47:09.491
for some people by deliberately
making them worse for others.

47:09.560 --> 47:10.686
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

47:16.960 --> 47:18.530
Well, I thought I might wear this.

47:22.560 --> 47:24.608
Oh, God. It's too much.
I'll try something more simple.

47:24.720 --> 47:26.404
No.Don%...

47:28.480 --> 47:30.687
Suddenly, I feel incompetent.

47:31.400 --> 47:34.404
I want the portrait to hang in the
office, so I want it to look formal.

47:34.480 --> 47:36.084
RUBEN: It's not formal.

47:36.920 --> 47:38.445
It's beautiful.

47:40.400 --> 47:41.606
It was made in Paris.

47:42.240 --> 47:43.844
It was stolen in Birmingham.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

47:44.160 --> 47:47.642
My mother stole it from a house
she was cleaning. 1901.

47:47.720 --> 47:49.131
RUBEN: No. No.

47:49.200 --> 47:50.964
It's yours. It belongs on you.

47:52.240 --> 47:54.447
A woman of substance and class.

47:54.520 --> 47:56.568
Believe me. I've painted many women

47:56.640 --> 47:58.722
who don't belong
in their expensive dresses.

48:00.960 --> 48:02.200
There'll be no charge.

48:02.880 --> 48:04.530
Your normal rate.

48:04.960 --> 48:07.122
- I insist.
- Hmm! There's a first.

48:09.520 --> 48:12.126
- So, when shall we start?
- I've already started.

48:13.200 --> 48:14.964
Come to my studio this evening.

48:15.080 --> 48:17.606
- POLLY: Uh, I am busy this evening.
- Polly, invite him.

48:18.640 --> 48:19.641
Invite me to what?

48:19.720 --> 48:21.722
Ada, this is a professional transaction.

48:21.800 --> 48:24.246
- Invite me to what?
- ADA: Shelby Foundation dinner.

48:24.320 --> 48:26.607
- Polly's going alone. You're invited...
- POLLY: Ada.

48:30.000 --> 48:32.480
I'll come to your studio on Sunday.

48:33.480 --> 48:35.448
And then we shall begin.

49:26.320 --> 49:28.527
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

49:37.360 --> 49:39.124
A woman of substance...

49:41.160 --> 49:42.491
...and class.

49:50.720 --> 49:52.802
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

50:00.120 --> 50:01.121
Hello.

50:02.840 --> 50:03.841
WOMAN: Hello, Polly.

50:12.080 --> 50:14.481
(1 N DISTIN CT)

50:20.120 --> 50:21.326
Tommy.

50:23.360 --> 50:25.567
Here's the leader
of the Birmingham City Council.

50:25.760 --> 50:27.125
- Hello, Tommy.
- Hi, Danny.

50:27.200 --> 50:28.486
DANIEL: How's business?

50:28.560 --> 50:30.688
TOMMY: All right, it's holding up,
holding up. How are you?

50:31.200 --> 50:32.326
You know each other?

50:33.040 --> 50:36.169
DANIEL: (CHUCKLES) I have interests
in a steelworks in Cradley Heath.

50:36.240 --> 50:39.722
Tommy helps me get my products
to the carmakers.

50:39.920 --> 50:42.651
Congratulations, Mrs Shelby,
on your wedding.

50:42.720 --> 50:44.961
Thank you,
I'm surprised you weren't invited.

50:45.040 --> 50:46.929
Now, how would that look, eh?

50:48.600 --> 50:51.490
Oh, now, the party has really started.

50:51.560 --> 50:52.721
Who are they?

50:52.880 --> 50:56.601
DANIEL: Father John Hughes
from St Mary's Boys Reformatory.

50:56.680 --> 50:59.889
And with him is Mr Patrickjarvis, MP.

50:59.960 --> 51:04.807
They are part of an organisation
called the Economic League.

51:04.880 --> 51:06.609
Did you invite them, Grace?

51:06.800 --> 51:08.290
Their names sound familiar.

51:09.160 --> 51:11.003
They were recommended by the Lord Mayor.

51:11.080 --> 51:14.289
Oh. On your
"best people of the city" list, eh?

51:14.480 --> 51:16.847
- GRACE: Do you know them?
- I'll introduce you, Tommy.

51:16.920 --> 51:20.322
That's all right, Danny.
I'll introduce myself.

51:34.560 --> 51:37.006
We appear to have taken you by surprise.

51:37.520 --> 51:39.170
I have adjusted.

51:40.760 --> 51:43.047
Since the socialists
got into Downing Street

51:43.120 --> 51:44.326
we are all being followed.

51:44.400 --> 51:46.687
We have to meet in places
where we'd meet anyway.

51:46.760 --> 51:48.091
You should have stopped by Small Heath.

51:48.160 --> 51:50.049
I could have given you
a more traditional welcome.

51:50.120 --> 51:53.647
- They want to know about ammunition.
- PATRICK: And chains for the wheels.

51:53.720 --> 51:56.200
When the White Guard
make their run for Tbilisi,

51:56.280 --> 51:57.884
it will be over rough terrain.

51:58.120 --> 52:01.647
(IN HALES SHARPLY) The chains are
suitable for snow or wet ground.

52:01.720 --> 52:03.529
They're already stored on the vehicles.

52:03.600 --> 52:05.489
There's a batch of weapons
set aside at the BSA,

52:05.560 --> 52:07.324
which is bound for the Turkish army.

52:07.640 --> 52:09.927
And how will you get it all aboard
the London train?

52:10.000 --> 52:12.241
There will be a strike that night
across the city.

52:13.000 --> 52:15.571
You will have to stop
the train twice. How?

52:16.360 --> 52:19.250
Two drivers willjoin the strike
at different points.

52:20.960 --> 52:26.251
Rather fun, getting the Communist unions
to help get weapons to the Whites.

52:26.320 --> 52:27.845
TOMMY: Yes, rather fun, eh?

52:29.200 --> 52:31.362
I am thinking ahead,
thinking of every possibility,

52:31.440 --> 52:33.249
remembering everything
that is happening.

52:33.360 --> 52:34.691
(PATRICK SCOFFS)

52:36.240 --> 52:38.561
The Russians want to inspect
the vehicles.

52:40.040 --> 52:42.361
- I'll take photographs.
- PATRICK: Mmm-mmm.

52:42.440 --> 52:45.489
The Duke has sent his niece, she's here.

52:46.400 --> 52:49.131
Tomorrow you will take her to the
factory and show her.

52:49.200 --> 52:52.886
No. Union conveners
are watching the factories.

52:54.760 --> 52:55.807
Not possible.

52:57.080 --> 53:00.209
Anything is possible, Mr Shelby.

53:00.280 --> 53:01.964
You will take her.

53:02.920 --> 53:05.321
You will pick her up
from this hotel at ten.

53:06.840 --> 53:09.650
Now, look, a priest with an empty glass.

53:11.000 --> 53:13.162
Let's get back to the party.

53:15.120 --> 53:20.160
You know, gentlemen, there is hell
and there is another place below hell.

53:21.960 --> 53:24.008
I will remember everything...

53:24.920 --> 53:26.649
And forget nothing.

53:31.320 --> 53:33.288
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

53:36.320 --> 53:37.606
GRACE: Tommy,

53:37.680 --> 53:39.887
this is Duchess Tatiana Petrovna.

53:40.040 --> 53:41.371
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

53:41.440 --> 53:43.602
Come on, Tommy, aren't you impressed
to meet a real duchess?

53:43.800 --> 53:45.723
Well, I understand they charge a fee.

53:45.960 --> 53:48.725
(SCOFFS) Mr Shelby,
you are very direct.

53:48.800 --> 53:50.086
Too direct.

53:50.160 --> 53:51.366
TATIANA: (CHUCKLES) But it's true.

53:52.000 --> 53:54.321
I attend these things for the champagne.

53:54.480 --> 53:56.881
And for the chance
to be treated like a duchess again.

53:57.240 --> 53:59.925
You should have kissed my hand,
Mr Shelby.

54:02.160 --> 54:03.525
Forgive me.

54:05.960 --> 54:07.724
She was asking about my sapphire.

54:07.800 --> 54:10.804
- I thought I recognised it.
- She said it was Russian.

54:10.880 --> 54:13.770
My husband has business in Russia.
Perhaps you know about it, Tatiana?

54:13.840 --> 54:15.649
Well, tonight is not a night
for business, eh?

54:15.720 --> 54:17.688
Is that why you were in the concert hall
for 10 minutes?

54:17.760 --> 54:19.046
I think people are ready
for dinner now, Grace.

54:19.240 --> 54:21.322
No, no. I'm not done
pumping people for money.

54:21.520 --> 54:22.931
What is "pump for money"?

54:23.080 --> 54:25.048
It's what I do every day.

54:25.720 --> 54:27.404
You know each other, do you?

54:28.360 --> 54:30.408
You see, I am in charge
of compiling the list of guests,

54:30.480 --> 54:32.767
but it's my husband
who seems to know all of them.

54:32.840 --> 54:34.365
I hear he is very well connected.

54:34.440 --> 54:36.329
And where does a duchess hear that?

54:36.480 --> 54:37.527
In certain circles.

54:37.600 --> 54:38.840
All right, enough. Ada.

54:38.960 --> 54:40.530
Grace, there's a Lady Dowager

54:40.600 --> 54:42.648
who wants to speak to you
about coffee mornings.

54:42.720 --> 54:44.961
She mentioned a Â£2,000 cash donation.

54:45.120 --> 54:47.248
Tatiana, you and I will speak later.

54:47.320 --> 54:48.845
TATIANA: I would like that.

54:51.080 --> 54:53.242
Going to the factory tomorrow
is a mistake.

54:54.280 --> 54:55.964
Nevertheless, we will go.

54:57.360 --> 55:00.682
Also, my uncle ordered me to seduce you
to give us an advantage.

55:00.760 --> 55:03.286
But with a beautiful wife like that
it will be difficult, no?

55:03.360 --> 55:04.850
Tomorrow is a mistake.

55:05.200 --> 55:07.680
Have you not heard?
We have no morals, we Russians.

55:07.880 --> 55:08.961
And no fucking sense.

55:09.040 --> 55:10.565
And no options.

55:11.040 --> 55:14.283
I would fuck you for the cause.
What do you think of that?

55:15.320 --> 55:17.527
I think you should not drink
vodka with champagne.

55:18.960 --> 55:21.327
TATIANA: Does your wife know
that the sapphire she is wearing

55:21.400 --> 55:23.448
has been cursed by a Gypsy?

55:24.440 --> 55:26.010
(CHUCKLING)

55:27.640 --> 55:28.641
What did you say?

55:29.040 --> 55:32.169
Nothing on Earth would make me wear it.

55:47.000 --> 55:49.162
Grace, listen to me.
Look, I can explain.

55:49.360 --> 55:50.361
- Go away.
- It's...

55:50.440 --> 55:51.646
MC: Ladies and gentlemen.

55:51.720 --> 55:52.881
For once, you shouldn't have to explain.

55:52.960 --> 55:56.328
The loyalty toast,
to His Majesty the King.

55:56.440 --> 55:58.204
ALL: To the King.

55:58.600 --> 56:00.125
MC: Dinner is served.

56:00.320 --> 56:02.368
TOMMY: You look beautiful,
but you need to take this off.

56:02.440 --> 56:04.010
Why? Because you think
it would look better on her?

56:04.080 --> 56:06.811
Grace, look at me,
fuck these people, eh.

56:06.880 --> 56:09.963
Fuck 'em, I need you to be all right.

56:10.280 --> 56:13.762
I need you, Grace. I need you.

56:21.080 --> 56:23.321
Damn you, Tommy Shelby. (CHUCKLES)

56:34.680 --> 56:36.170
(CHUCKLES)

56:36.240 --> 56:37.765
- Shall we go inside?
- Yeah.

56:40.880 --> 56:42.325
For Angel!

56:43.840 --> 56:45.001
(GUNSHOT)

56:45.200 --> 56:47.123
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

56:55.640 --> 56:58.883
Get me a fucking ambulance now!

57:41.640 --> 57:43.642
(THEME SONG PLAYING)
